@anchor{@strong{@asis{}-@asis{}-@asis{}tag}}

Tag lines with arguments.

Each output line will be prepended with the arguments and TAB
(\t). When combined with @strong{@asis{}-@asis{}-@asis{}onall} or @strong{@asis{}-@asis{}-@asis{}nonall} the lines will be
prepended with the sshlogin instead.

@strong{@asis{}-@asis{}-@asis{}tag} is ignored when using @strong{-u}.

See also: @strong{@asis{}-@asis{}-@asis{}tagstring} @strong{@asis{}-@asis{}-@asis{}ctag}

@item @strong{@asis{}-@asis{}-@asis{}tagstring} @emph{str}
@anchor{@strong{@asis{}-@asis{}-@asis{}tagstring} @emph{str}}

Tag lines with a string.

Each output line will be prepended with @emph{str} and TAB (\t). @emph{str}
can contain replacement strings such as @strong{@{@}}.

@strong{@asis{}-@asis{}-@asis{}tagstring} is ignored when using @strong{-u}, @strong{@asis{}-@asis{}-@asis{}onall}, and @strong{@asis{}-@asis{}-@asis{}nonall}.

See also: @strong{@asis{}-@asis{}-@asis{}tag} @strong{@asis{}-@asis{}-@asis{}ctagstring}

@item @strong{@asis{}-@asis{}-@asis{}tee}
@anchor{@strong{@asis{}-@asis{}-@asis{}tee}}

Pipe all data to all jobs.

Used with @strong{@asis{}-@asis{}-@asis{}pipe}/@strong{@asis{}-@asis{}-@asis{}pipe-part} and @strong{:::}.

@verbatim
  seq 1000 | parallel --pipe --tee -v wc {} ::: -w -l -c
@end verbatim

How many numbers in 1..1000 contain 0..9, and how many bytes do they
fill:

@verbatim
  seq 1000 | parallel --pipe --tee --tag \
    'grep {1} | wc {2}' ::: {0..9} ::: -l -c
@end verbatim

How many words contain a..z and how many bytes do they fill?

@verbatim
  parallel -a /usr/share/dict/words --pipe-part --tee --tag \
    'grep {1} | wc {2}' ::: {a..z} ::: -l -c
@end verbatim

See also: @strong{:::} @strong{@asis{}-@asis{}-@asis{}pipe} @strong{@asis{}-@asis{}-@asis{}pipe-part}

@item @strong{@asis{}-@asis{}-@asis{}term-seq} @emph{sequence}
@anchor{@strong{@asis{}-@asis{}-@asis{}term-seq} @emph{sequence}}

Termination sequence.

When a job is killed due to @strong{@asis{}-@asis{}-@asis{}timeout}, @strong{@asis{}-@asis{}-@asis{}memfree}, @strong{@asis{}-@asis{}-@asis{}halt}, or
abnormal termination of GNU @strong{parallel}, @emph{sequence} determines how
the job is killed. The default is:

@verbatim
    TERM,200,TERM,100,TERM,50,KILL,25
@end verbatim

which sends a TERM signal, waits 200 ms, sends another TERM signal,
waits 100 ms, sends another TERM signal, waits 50 ms, sends a KILL
signal, waits 25 ms, and exits. GNU @strong{parallel} detects if a process
dies before the waiting time is up.

See also: @strong{@asis{}-@asis{}-@asis{}halt} @strong{@asis{}-@asis{}-@asis{}timeout} @strong{@asis{}-@asis{}-@asis{}memfree}

